  n=7: floor(n/4) = 1
  n=8: floor(n/4) = 2
  n=9: floor(n/4) = 2
  n=10: floor(n/4) = 2
  n=11: floor(n/4) = 2
  n=12: floor(n/4) = 3

beta_3 <= 2 holds through n=9 (sampling).
floor(n/4) bound: 1,1,1,2,2,2,2,3 for n=5..12
beta_3 first exceeds 1 at n=8 (floor(8/4)=2). Consistent!
Prediction: beta_3 <= 2 should hold through n=11.
beta_3 = 3 first possible at n=12 if floor(n/4) is correct.

